# Vendo as variaveis

# age in days
# gender 1 - women, 2 - men
# height cm
# weight kg
# ap_hi Systolic blood pressure
# ap_lo Diastolic blood pressure
# cholesterol 1: normal, 2: above normal, 3: well above normal
# gluc 1: normal, 2: above normal, 3: well above normal
# smoke whether patient smokes or not
# alco Binary feature
# active Binary feature
# cardio Target variable

Ajuste de parâmetros

levels(cardio_train_fil$cardio) <- c("No", "Yes")
levels(cardio_test_fil$cardio) <- c("No", "Yes")

# Escolher o melhor cp 

set.seed(123)
ctrl <- trainControl(method = "repeatedcv", 
                     number = 10,
                     repeats = 3,
                     rpart.control(minsplit = 10, minbucket = 5), #minsplit: the minimum number of observations that must exist in a node in order for a split to be attempted. minbucket: the minimum number of observations in any terminal <leaf> node.
                     classProbs = TRUE,
                           ## Evaluate performance using 
                           ## the following function
                           summaryFunction = twoClassSummary)
dtFit <- train(cardio ~ .,
      method     = "rpart",
      parms = list(split = "gini"),
      tuneLength = 20,
      trControl  = ctrl,
      metric     = "ROC",
      data       = cardio_train_fil)
dtFit

# Curva ROC

dtPredict2 <- predict(dtFit, newdata = cardio_test_fil[,!names(cardio_test_fil) %in% "cardio"], type = "prob")

dtROC
## 
## Call:
## roc.default(response = cardio_test_fil$cardio, predictor = dtPredict2[,     "Yes"])
##

plot.roc(dtROC, print.thres = "best", legacy.axes = T)

result <- as.factor(ifelse(dtPredict2[,"Yes"] > coords(dtROC, "best", ret = "threshold", transpose = T), "Yes", "No"))

ctrl <- trainControl(method = "repeatedcv", 
                     number = 10,
                     repeats = 3)
dtFit <- train(Species ~ .,
      method     = "rpart",
      tuneLength = 20,
      trControl  = ctrl,
      metric = "Kappa",
      data = train.data)
